		<title type="html"><![CDATA[My tattoo quote translation.]]></title>
		<link rel="alternate" href="http://spokensanskrit.de/board/forum/viewtopic.php?pid=714#p714"/>
		<content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I&#039;m planning on getting a tattoo in Sanskrit of the quote I wrote myself. If someone could PLEASE help translate this quote, it&#039;d be greatly appreciated.</p><p>The quote is:</p><p>Though we spark like the storms collide, though we hurt but never speak and though we are.. who we are. Never will I collide with another, never will I be closed with my heart and never will I lose who I am nor forget you.</p><p>What I have so far is,<br />यद्यपि&#160; though<br />वयम्&#160; we<br />स्फुल्लिङ्ग&#160; spark<br />सदृश&#160; like<br />चण्डवात&#160; storm<br />उत&#160; and<br />हिंसा&#160; hurt<br />परन्तु&#160; but<br />जातु . never<br />वदति { वद् }&#160; speak<br />वर्तामहे { वृत् }&#160; we are<br />यक&#160; who<br />इच्छा . will<br />अस्मद् . I<br />सह . with<br />पर . another<br />जातु&#160; never<br />अस्ति { अस् } be<br />निद्राण . closed<br />मदीय . my<br />हृदय&#160; heart<br />पराजयते&#160; lose<br />अहम् अस्मि&#160; I am.<br />विस्मरति { वि- स्मृ }&#160; forget<br />त्वम् . you</p><p>The only words I couldn&#039;t find were, &quot;the&quot;, &quot;collide&quot; and &quot;nor&quot;. What other words would be similar to those that I could replace them with but have the same general meaning? If there&#039;s any mistakes, please do correct! The last thing I want is to have an incorrect quote tattooed on my body. Also, what do the bracketed scripts mean?</p>]]></content>
